title: Day 633
content:
# Day 633

Today was a solid Friday I got to enjoy free BBQ for lunch at my job (shout out my team lead). Later, I enjoyed a delightful dinner with my partner, father, and child, which was the highlight of my evening. I'm filled with gratitude for these moments.

The dinner was so delicious and comforting that I accidentally dozed off while putting my daughter to bed. Now I'm up to finish my writing for the day.

I don't have much to write about. I'll note my seven books by Robert Greene came in. Looking forward to reading those. I started the first page of War and it was fascinating. It made the point we prepare for peace but life is war. Something that seems so obvious yet something I would wager most of us never even consider.

![](https://miro.medium.com/0*uwtNqUvfPeQhvSVd.jpg)

12/15/23

Conor Jay Chepenik
